Heard this on a cassette tape audiobook as a child and it's always stuck with me. Orson Scott Card is one of my favorite authors, highly recommend the Enders series</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XjkKXWi</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[NoahTheMask]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I was adopted!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/IYpkugM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XzQrWOI.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This handsome gentleman showed up at my door like, “you will now house, feed, and love me.”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5kWXS6f.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>… and he was right.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pFyk502.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>MAKING BISCUITS. How dare he be so charming.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/I4cKlPr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IarMfP2.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He showed up last week in below 0 weather, so of course I was going to bring him in. Took him to a vet right away to check for a chip, and he has none. Also isn’t neutered so it was very likely he’s a stray with no owner. Contacted the local shelters and animal control as well as posted in several spots, but no one claimed the little man. 

I was able to get him into the vet today and he was given a clean bill of health! 

Next step is introducing him to the queen of the house, my senior cat Chloe. It’s going to be challenging but well worth it. 

Welcome home, George!

Edit: I also asked around the neighborhood and people have seen him out an about for a while, and no one seems to know of an owner. Based on his behavior (used the litter box right away, no accidents, comfortable with people after an initial timid introduction, etc) I would swear he’s been domesticated. Sad to think someone would have just abandoned him. Really wish I knew his story! 

